# Project Coding Standards

## Architecture
This project uses **clean / hexagonal architecture** (ports-and-adapters).
The Dependency Rule is the invariant: dependencies always point **inward**.

## Layer Boundaries
- `core/` → Pure domain. ZERO external imports.
- `application/` → Imports from `core` only. Services use UoW properties (`uow.users`).
- `ports/` → FastAPI routes, DI container. Wires concrete adapters.
- `adapters/` → DB repos, cache, HTTP clients. Implements core protocols.
- `infrastructure/` → DB engines, HTTP clients, security, profiling.

## Python Standards
- Python {{ python_version }}+, keyword-only args (`*` separator), `ParseableEnum` for enums
- `from __future__ import annotations` in every file
- Full type hints, Google-style docstrings, `structlog` for logging
- No `Any`, no relative imports (except `__init__.py`), no `print()`

## TypeScript Standards
- Strict mode, no `any`, Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first `@theme {}`)
- {{ frontend_framework | capitalize }} components with typed props

## Testing
- pytest markers: `@pytest.mark.unit`, `integration`, `property`, `performance`
- Factories via `factory_boy`, property tests via `Hypothesis`
- Coverage ≥ 80% on `core` + `application` layers

## Naming Registry
- `registry/naming_registry.json` is the single source of truth
- Run `task registry:generate` after any registry changes
- Never hand-edit generated constant files
